The paper deals with downlink channel estimation in FDD-based massive MIMO systems, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), system and control theory (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and communication (cs.COM). The use of cascaded precoding and parametric models also suggests a focus on signal processing and optimization, which are common in the cs.IT and cs.SY sub-categories. Therefore, cs.IT and cs.SY are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.NI, cs.MM, and cs.COM.
